reviews.review_text:
bread crumb Althea is, for me, the essence of the Grateful Dead with Brent at the keys.  Right from this first live version you can tell that this will have staying power.

Lost Sailor, also presented here for the first time was played 4 times without Saint of Circumstance.  Twice with Deal, once with Althea (I can't wait to hear that one) and once stand alone.  Once they got it right, they never broke the pairing.  Kind of like Scarlet > Fire - it just makes musical sense.
Sweet as honey This show is layers and layers of the sweetest Garcia to be found anywhere...
A Little History This is the first show that Tiger, a custom guitar built by Doug Irwin, was used.
